# Agentic Rules — Architecture Overview

This project uses **Vertical Slices** with a **Functional Core / Imperative Shell**: pure domain logic, NestJS for orchestration, typed I/O at boundaries. Cursor loads detailed rules from separate files (better RAG chunks). **Always read the rule file** that matches the layer you are editing.

Rules are classified under `rules/` using the AIDD-style buckets: **01** fundamentals, **02** TypeScript & pure domain, **03** frameworks & libraries (NestJS, boundaries, slices), **04** tools & configuration. `.cursor/rules/` mirrors these files via symlinks.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| Shell | NestJS (`@Injectable` use cases, controllers, modules) |
| Core | `fp-ts` and/or `Effect` — errors as values in domain |
| Validation | Zod or `@effect/schema` at HTTP/persistence edges |

## Canonical layout

```text
src/
  modules/
    <feature>/
      domain/                    # Pure functions only — Rules 1–4
        <feature>.model.ts       # Or <feature>.domain.ts if <5 pure functions
        <feature>.logic.ts
      application/
        use-cases/               # Rule 5 — orchestration, pipes
      infrastructure/
        persistence/             # Rule 6 — sql_* repositories
        http/                    # Rule 6 — controllers, DTOs, http_* gateways
  shared/
    domain/                      # Cross-cutting types — Rule 7
    infrastructure/              # Shared clients
```

